The White House has announced that Angella Reid will be the next Director of the President's Executive Residence and "Chief Usher." Reid will be the first woman to serve in this role and brings 25 years of hotel management experience. She will be responsible for overseeing all aspects of operations and activities within the Executive Residence and grounds, including managing resources efficiently, maintaining relationships with related entities, and overseeing the annual inventory of White House property. Reid currently serves as General Manager at The Ritz-Carlton, Pentagon City, and has held management positions at other Ritz-Carlton properties as well as other hotels. She holds a degree in Hospitality Management and is conversational in German and basic Spanish.